<document>

 <properties>
  <title>Apache James Server 3 - Indexer Configuration</title>
 </properties>

<body>

  <section name="Indexer Configuration">

      This configuration applies only to Spring wiring.

    <p>Consult <a href="https://github.com/apache/james-project/tree/master/server/app/src/main/resources/indexer.xml">indexer.xml</a> in GIT to get some examples and hints.</p>
    
    <p>Use this configuration to define the type of mailbox indexer used to search the user's mails.</p>
    
    <p>Under indexer tag, define the provider.</p>

      <dl>
        <dt><strong>provider</strong></dt>
        <dd>Supported providers are: luceneSearch (default), lazyIndex (built on top of full mailbox content iterations).</dd>
      </dl>
  </section>

</body>

</document>

